        <h2>Custom home sites in Montana's beautiful Northwest corner</h2>
        <span class="team-content">Lake Creek Ranches is a gated community of custom 3 to 15 acre home sites located near Troy, Montana.  Two of these home sites have Lake Creek frontage for fishing out your back door.  It's a picturesque setting, halfway between Sandpoint, Idaho and Kalispell, Montana, gateway to Glacier National Park.  The Bull Lake Valley is a world class destination for fishing and hunting enthusiasts alike.  With the Cabinet Mountain trails, Bull Lake, and the Kootenai River just minutes away, there are ample opportunities for enjoying the great outdoors in this quiet corner of Montana.  The first custom home on a 3 acre horse property is now available and is being sold fully furnished.  The main house and guest log cabin offer over 2,500 square feet of living space for you and your guests to relax in.  This tastefully designed home is a perfect combination of modern amenities and rustic charm.  Schweitzer Mountain Ski Resort is scenic 65 mile drive from the property.  Enjoy hiking in the nearby Ross Creek Cedar Grove.  Launch your boat at the pristine Bull Lake, just a few miles away.  The possibilities are endless, stop dreaming about Montana and come see it for yourself!</span>
